 into how the `SchemaTypeSystemImpl` constructor works with the `holderClass`, which searches resources through its class loader. It seems that if the child loader delegates to the parent, it could suffice. However, I need to clarify whether the type system implementation class is loaded by the child or parent loader. \\n\\nThe loading process involves `Class.forName`, and it’s crucial that `TypeSystemHolder` works correctly. I’m also contemplating using reflection to access fields of the loaded class. I might consider `MethodHandles`, but since it’s an internal class, the lack of a public API complicates things. Plus, I’m worried about potential errors in a native image when trying to define class bytes at runtime. I need to keep an eye on that!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering Native Image Resources**\\n\\nI'm wondering if, in a native image, reading resources and using `defineClass` will actually work with the available resources. The class resource might be there, but I need to be careful about catching just the right errors, like an `AssertionError` for a missing resource. \\n\\nThe developer mentions that tests execute under the native image by default, which is encouraging. I'll need to ensure I'm not being too broad in my error handling. Maybe it’s best to replace the existing test with two more targeted tests? That could help clarify things!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_TJWkHgrFoqgGKNUZr3HMbWUl|fc_0b413c8573a909410169ff856598ac819f855bbef42d8298a4", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.poi/poi-ooxml-schemas/4.1.2/src/test/java/org_apache_poi/poi_ooxml_schemas/SchemaorgApacheXmlbeansSystemSD023D6490046BA0250A839A9AD24C443TypeSystemHolderTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import com.microsoft.schemas.compatibility.AlternateContentDocument;\nimport org.apache.xmlbeans.SchemaTypeSystem;\nimport org.apache.xmlbeans.XmlBeans;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class SchemaorgApacheXmlbeansSystemS